'''Dariusz Dudka''' ({{IPA-pol|ËdarjuÊ Ëdutka}}; born [[December 9]], [[1983]] in [[Kostrzyn nad OdrÄ ]]) is a [[Poles|Polish]] [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who currently plays for [[AJ Auxerre]] and the [[Poland national football team|Polish national football team]] as a defensive midfielder or full-back. He can also play as a centre back.
==Career==
He began his career in 1999/2000 for his home team, before moving in 2000/01 to [[Amica Wronki]]. He made his debut in April 2000 for Amica Wronki. He appeared over 70 times for [[Wisla KrakÃ³w]]. In June 2008 he joined [[AJ Auxerre]].
He has 58 [[cap (sport)|caps]] to his name for the [[Poland national football team|Polish national team]], and played in both the [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] and [[Euro 2008]].
